Yeah, the register used to access PPU memory (accessed through $2006) is used during rendering. Anything you do with it during rendering will mess the current display and you'll probably not suceed on what you were trying to do.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun May 28, 2006 8:25 pm</p><hr />
